The paper introduces a method to intelligently schedule a stream of tasks to available processing elements in a heterogeneous system-on-chip (SoC) using deep reinforcement learning. This involves complex sequential decision making, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of coprocessors in the SoC also suggests that the paper could belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) sub-category. The paper also deals with scheduling tasks, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning for decision making could also place the paper in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
